Had an original size A Wreck, a side of Mac n' Cheese with mushrooms, medium unsweetened iced tea and a pumpkin cookie.  The sandwich was ok, I enjoyed the bread, though the meat and toppings were pretty skimpy. If that's the amount in an original I can't imagine what the skinny option, which supposedly has 1/3 less meat, is like. Toppings were also few and I didn't get pickles as I requested. What the sandwich had plenty of was mayonnaise. Kind of too much mayo. Basically, it seemed like a mayo sandwich with a few toppings.  Mac n' Cheese was ok. Kinda dried out and lukewarm. I'll admit it was just about an hour before closing (I know, I know - it was the only place in waking distance) but still, don't serve subpar food no matter how ready you are to go home. Mushrooms on the Mac n'Cheese were the same - lukewarm, obliviously cooked many hours ago.  Pumpkin cookie was good, flavorful, soft, iced tea was pretty basic. Not bad but not very good.  Considering my lack of choices at the moment, I was ok with what I paid, would've liked a better sandwich, though.
